            "title": "Leading Apparel Brands Back unspun’s Plans to Build Domestic Manufacturing Hubs for Automated Apparel Production in the U.S.",
            "id": "4347ecbb-0790-4384-a76b-0e562a30122f",
            "description": "In San Francisco, several major brands like Walmart have expressed their support for unspun's initiative to enhance domestic manufacturing in the United States. This involves utilizing AI-driven 3D weaving technology to facilitate apparel production closer to consumers on a larger scale. Key supply chain collaborators such as Bethel Industries, Peckham, and PDS Ltd / GSC Link are actively involved in setting up automated domestic production centers, with the commencement of initial production expected in the near future.",
